WEBVTT

00:05.189 --> 00:08.156
You have a call
with the PBA chief at 1:00,

00:08.157 --> 00:10.792
you have a briefing
with TARU at 3:00 p.m.,

00:10.794 --> 00:12.693
and an intelligence meeting
directly after.

00:16.200 --> 00:17.900
Bad news.

00:17.902 --> 00:18.734
How do you know?

00:18.736 --> 00:20.002
I just know. Gimme.

00:20.004 --> 00:21.136
An off-duty cop,

00:21.138 --> 00:22.871
Officer Kevin Olivet,
shot and killed

00:22.873 --> 00:24.907
a 32-year-old female
at a pharmacy

00:24.909 --> 00:28.644
on East 96th Street
at approximately 600 hours.

00:28.646 --> 00:31.580
The victim was unarmed--
no knife, no gun--

00:31.582 --> 00:33.181
and the press
is swarming.

00:33.183 --> 00:35.050
Why did the officer use
deadly force?

00:35.052 --> 00:36.351
The victim was shoplifting,

00:36.353 --> 00:38.754
and when the officer tried to
intervene, it became physical.

00:38.756 --> 00:40.556
So shot
in the commission of a crime?

00:40.558 --> 00:41.757
Victim have a record?

00:41.759 --> 00:44.459
Assault, four counts
of robbery dating back

00:44.461 --> 00:47.496
to 2013, possession
with intent to sell,

00:47.498 --> 00:49.531
and aggravated harassment.

00:49.533 --> 00:52.434
Our new mayor isn't going
to like this.

00:52.436 --> 00:53.735
<b><font color="#FF0080">GORMLEY:</font></b>
What does a public

00:53.737 --> 00:55.170
advocate know about governing?

00:55.172 --> 00:56.405
They know how it's gonna play

00:56.407 --> 00:58.440
to the eight and a half million
of us who aren't cops.

00:58.442 --> 01:01.843
Oh, so we're gonna alienate
35,000 of us who are cops?

01:01.845 --> 01:03.378
It was a police action.

01:03.380 --> 01:05.379
Yes.
And police actions...

01:05.382 --> 01:06.949
Don't have
a political component.

01:06.951 --> 01:10.786
But maybe we can be a little
more measured in our response.

01:10.788 --> 01:15.457
We will handle this one
exactly the way we always have.

01:15.459 --> 01:17.759
<b><font color="#FF0080">DANNY:</font></b>
<i>Do I need</i>

01:17.761 --> 01:20.762
to remind you that your
ex-husband is not very reliable?

01:20.764 --> 01:22.998
Jack is a lot
of things,

01:23.000 --> 01:24.733
but he would never
stand me up.

01:24.735 --> 01:26.868
And he's not answering my calls,
and he always answers.

01:26.870 --> 01:28.804
Look, Erin, I know what
you're up to, okay,

01:28.806 --> 01:32.007
and no amount of busywork is
gonna keep my mind off of Linda.

01:32.009 --> 01:33.208
That's not
what I'm doing.

01:33.210 --> 01:34.710
Of course it's
what you're doing.

01:34.712 --> 01:36.678
It's what the entire
family's doing.

01:36.680 --> 01:38.647
I know
you don't like Jack, but...

01:38.649 --> 01:41.850
What would make you think
I don't like... jackass?

01:41.852 --> 01:43.385
Something isn't right.

01:43.387 --> 01:45.354
- Well, did you call his assistant?
- Yeah.

01:45.356 --> 01:46.688
She's not answering, either.

01:46.690 --> 01:48.490
<font color="#0CEC0C">(phone ringing)</font>
This his office?

01:48.492 --> 01:50.058
Yeah.

01:50.060 --> 01:54.196
<font color="#0CEC0C">(phone ringing)</font>

01:54.198 --> 01:55.430
Jack!

01:55.432 --> 01:56.898
Oh, my God. Jack?

01:56.900 --> 01:58.433
<font color="#FF5500">(panting)</font>
Call 911.

01:58.435 --> 02:00.636
<font color="#FF5500">(Erin gasps)</font>

02:03.173 --> 02:04.940
<font color="#FF5500">(panting)</font>

02:04.942 --> 02:06.141
Call 911.

02:06.143 --> 02:08.342
<font color="#FF5500">(panting)</font>

02:11.615 --> 02:13.315
When I rode with Welch,
I drove.

02:13.317 --> 02:14.916
That was then,
this is now.

02:14.918 --> 02:16.546
He liked that I drove.

02:16.570 --> 02:18.488
And you could always go
back to riding with him.

02:18.489 --> 02:20.822
Why? You want to go back
to riding with Patimkin?

02:20.824 --> 02:22.991
I didn't say that.
Because you missed me.

02:22.993 --> 02:24.593
I didn't say
that, either.

02:24.595 --> 02:25.794
Didn't have to.

02:25.796 --> 02:27.129
<font color="#808080">MALE DISPATCHER:</font>
12-David, welcome back.

02:27.131 --> 02:28.930
We have a 10-54, an OD

02:28.932 --> 02:31.233
on West 23rd Street
and West Side Highway.

02:31.235 --> 02:32.968
12-David responding.

02:32.970 --> 02:35.637
And it's good
to be back, Central.

02:35.639 --> 02:37.773
<font color="#0CEC0C">(siren blaring)</font>

02:37.775 --> 02:40.042
♪ ♪

02:40.044 --> 02:41.276
Did you call 911?
<font color="#808080">MAN:</font> Yeah, it was me.

02:41.278 --> 02:42.244
I called.

02:42.246 --> 02:43.578
Please, my girlfriend--
she needs help.

02:43.580 --> 02:45.480
All right, let's go.

02:45.482 --> 02:47.916
Step aside. Excuse me.
Step back.

02:47.918 --> 02:49.317
Police.
Coming through.

02:49.319 --> 02:51.086
Right behind you.
Police.

02:51.088 --> 02:53.255
Step aside.

02:54.391 --> 02:55.991
Jamie, I got this.

02:55.993 --> 02:57.259
Stay here.

02:57.261 --> 02:59.995
Hey, sweetheart, what's
your name? What's your name?

02:59.997 --> 03:01.163
Everyone, back up.

03:01.165 --> 03:04.266
♪ ♪

03:04.268 --> 03:06.535
Is this her?

03:06.537 --> 03:08.503
What's your girlfriend's name?
It's Taylor.

03:08.505 --> 03:12.007
Hey, Taylor, can you hear me?
Taylor, what'd you take? Hey!

03:12.009 --> 03:13.208
<b><font color="#FF0080">JANKO:</font></b>
Come on.

03:13.210 --> 03:15.644
Hey, kill the music!
Shut the music off!

03:15.646 --> 03:17.312
Shut it off!
<font color="#FF5500">(music stops)</font>

03:17.314 --> 03:19.815
<font color="#FF5500">(woman groaning)</font>

03:22.419 --> 03:25.821
<font color="#FF5500">(overlapping chatter)</font>

03:27.124 --> 03:28.490
Eddie, call it in.

03:28.492 --> 03:31.760
Central, 12-David. 10-85.
Requesting additional units

03:31.762 --> 03:33.028
at this location.

03:33.030 --> 03:35.897
<font color="#FF5500">(sighs)</font>
And put a rush on that bus!

